WEBVTT

00:01.434 --> 00:04.037
THE FINAL SECONDS
TICK OF THE CLOCK.

00:04.104 --> 00:06.339
THE GOATS HAVE DONE IT -- 12-0.

00:06.406 --> 00:08.475
A PERFECT SEASON
FOR COACH MARTY DANIELS

00:08.541 --> 00:10.710
AND THE NUMBER-ONE-RANKED
BLUE MOUNTAIN STATE,

00:10.777 --> 00:12.512
AND THEY DID IT BEHIND THE ARM

00:12.579 --> 00:14.714
OF BACKUP QUARTERBACK
ALEX MORAN.

00:14.781 --> 00:16.650
SIMPLY INCREDIBLE.

00:16.716 --> 00:17.717
AND THE --

00:17.784 --> 00:19.486
[ TV SHUTS OFF ]

00:20.720 --> 00:22.021
[ DOORS OPEN ]

00:22.089 --> 00:24.191
[ CHEERING,
INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

00:35.368 --> 00:37.037
CALM DOWN, CALM DOWN.

00:37.104 --> 00:39.339
THEY SAID I COULDN´T DO IT.

00:39.406 --> 00:40.740
THEY SAID I WAS WASHED UP.

00:40.807 --> 00:44.344
WELL, THEY CAN KISS MY ASS,
BECAUSE WE´RE NUMBER ONE!

00:44.411 --> 00:46.613
[ CHEERING ]

00:46.679 --> 00:48.514
WHERE´S MORAN?

00:48.581 --> 00:49.449
WHERE´S MORAN?

00:49.516 --> 00:50.450
HMM?

00:50.517 --> 00:51.751
I GOT TO BE HONEST, SON.

00:51.818 --> 00:54.221
I DIDN´T EXPECT TOO MUCH
FROM YOU TODAY.

00:54.287 --> 00:56.089
BUT YOU PLAYED A HELL OF A GAME.

00:56.156 --> 00:58.291
I´M AS SURPRISED
AS YOU ARE, COACH.

00:58.358 --> 01:00.427
BUT IT ALL WOULD HAVE BEEN
FOR NOTHING

01:00.493 --> 01:04.029
IF IT WASN´T FOR THE GAME-SAVING
GOAL-LINE TACKLE

01:04.097 --> 01:05.665
BY OUR CAPTAIN, THAD CASTLE.

01:05.732 --> 01:07.301
COME ON
AND GET YOUR GAME BALL, SON.

01:07.367 --> 01:09.669
[ CHEERING ]

01:09.736 --> 01:11.505
THANK YOU, COACH.

01:11.571 --> 01:16.008
YOU KNOW, THIS MIGHT HAVE BEEN
MY LAST GAME EVER HERE AT B.M.S.

01:16.076 --> 01:19.346
THERE´S A LOT I WANT TO SAY
ABOUT MY CAREER HERE

01:19.412 --> 01:21.214
AND THE SEASON AS A WHOLE,

01:21.281 --> 01:25.017
BUT LET´S SAVE THE WATERWORKS
FOR WHEN THE REPORTERS GET HERE.

01:25.084 --> 01:26.786
ALL RIGHT, BUDDY, LISTEN --

01:26.853 --> 01:29.289
SO YOU´RE JUST GONNA GIVE THAD
THE GAME BALL?

01:29.356 --> 01:31.525
HE´S THE ONE
WHO INJURED MY SHOULDER.

01:31.591 --> 01:33.726
I CARRIED THIS TEAM
THE WHOLE SEASON!

01:33.793 --> 01:35.795
I SHOULD BE GETTING
THAT GAME BALL!

01:35.862 --> 01:37.697
YEAH, SHOULDA, COULDA, WOULDA.

01:37.764 --> 01:39.366
HELL WITH THIS TEAM.

01:40.733 --> 01:44.404
HEY, RADON, WAIT A MINUTE.

01:44.471 --> 01:46.206
THEY´RE GOING CRAZY OUT THERE.

01:46.273 --> 01:47.141
WHO´S GOING CRAZY?

01:47.207 --> 01:49.676
OH, YEAH!
LET´S GO!

01:49.742 --> 01:51.111
GET THAT ASSHOLE OUT OF HERE.

01:51.178 --> 01:53.313
-OH, YEAH! WHOO!
-[ DOOR SLAMS ]

01:53.380 --> 01:56.082
IT´S A RIOT!

01:56.149 --> 01:58.251
[ REV THEORY´S "HELL YEAH"
PLAYS ]

01:58.318 --> 01:59.519
CAN YOU FEEL THAT?

02:02.555 --> 02:04.124
YOU BETTER HOLD ON.

02:04.191 --> 02:06.326
THIS ONE´S ABOUT TO GET BUMPY.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.062
♪ GIVE ME A "HELL" ♪

02:09.129 --> 02:10.096
♪ GIVE ME A "YEAH" ♪

02:10.163 --> 02:10.830
♪ HELL, YEAH ♪

02:10.897 --> 02:12.766
♪ STAND UP RIGHT NOW ♪

02:12.832 --> 02:14.434
♪ GIVE ME A "HELL" ♪

02:14.501 --> 02:16.670
♪ GIVE ME A "YEAH" ♪

02:16.736 --> 02:18.171
♪ STAND UP RIGHT NOW ♪

02:18.238 --> 02:19.839
♪ GIVE ME A "HELL" ♪

02:19.906 --> 02:22.376
♪ GIVE ME A "YEAH" ♪

02:22.442 --> 02:24.744
♪ STAND UP RIGHT NOW ♪

02:27.347 --> 02:29.782
WHAT THE HELL?

02:29.849 --> 02:31.718
WHAT´S GOING ON OUTSIDE?

02:31.784 --> 02:34.754
IT´S PROBABLY JUST THE MEDIA
TRYING TO INTERVIEW ME.

02:34.821 --> 02:35.789
ARE YOU SERIOUS RIGHT NOW?

02:35.855 --> 02:37.524
YEAH.

02:37.590 --> 02:39.625
[  CHEERING  ]

02:44.464 --> 02:47.767
YOU ARE WITNESSING WHAT APPEARS
TO BE THE BIGGEST SPORTS RIOT

02:47.834 --> 02:51.104
BLUE MOUNTAIN STATE HAS SEEN
IN NEARLY 20 YEARS.

02:51.170 --> 02:53.139
THE LAST SUCH RIOT AT B.M.S.

02:53.206 --> 02:58.444
RESULTED IN $500,000 WORTH
OF DAMAGES, 39 INJURIES,

02:58.511 --> 03:01.146
AND, OF COURSE,
THE WORST TRAGEDY OF ALL --

03:01.214 --> 03:03.349
THE BELOVED
MOUNTAIN GOAT MASCOT

03:03.416 --> 03:07.253
WAS MAULED AND HUNG FROM
THE FOOTBALL HOUSE BALCONY.

03:10.257 --> 03:13.627
I´M JULIA KING,
AND I´M REPORTING LIVE --

03:13.693 --> 03:16.396
OH, MY GOD.
WHERE´S SAMMY?

03:16.463 --> 03:18.665
[ SCREAMING ]

03:23.436 --> 03:25.771
[ CROWD SCREAMING ]

03:47.727 --> 03:48.761
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

03:48.828 --> 03:50.463
WHAT THE HELL ARE THEY
RIOTING FOR OUT THERE?

03:50.530 --> 03:51.464
WE WON!

03:51.531 --> 03:53.866
THE BIGGEST SPORTS RIOTS
IN HISTORY HAPPEN AFTER WINS --

03:53.933 --> 03:56.469
IOWA STATE, MARYLAND, L.A.

03:56.536 --> 03:58.705
I´LL CALL ALEX.
HE´LL COME FOR US.

03:58.771 --> 04:00.473
DAMN IT.
NO SIGNAL.

04:00.540 --> 04:02.742
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK ALEX MORAN
WOULD COME FOR SOMEONE LIKE YOU?

04:02.809 --> 04:04.778
IF HE´S COMING FOR ANYONE,
HE´S COMING FOR US.

04:04.844 --> 04:06.746
-WE´RE PRACTICALLY DATING HIM.
-WE´RE PRACTICALLY DATING HIM.

04:06.813 --> 04:08.715
GUYS, ALEX ISN´T COMING
FOR ANYBODY.

04:08.781 --> 04:10.383
HE THREW FOUR TOUCHDOWN PASSES.

04:10.450 --> 04:12.319
HE´S PROBABLY OUT THERE
PARTYING HIS ASS OFF

04:12.385 --> 04:14.620
WITH THE REST OF ´EM.

04:14.687 --> 04:16.789
HE´LL COME FOR US.

04:16.856 --> 04:18.358
I KNOW IT.

04:18.425 --> 04:21.695
I CAN´T TAKE THIS ANYMORE.
I GOT TO GO FIND SAMMY.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.663
THERE´S A GOOD CHANCE
HE´S ALREADY DEAD, MORAN.

04:23.730 --> 04:25.465
YOU SHOULD JUST WAIT HERE
FOR THE REPORTERS.

04:25.532 --> 04:27.667
I´M SURE THEY´LL BE INTERESTED
IN TALKING TO YOU, TOO,

04:27.734 --> 04:30.236
ESPECIALLY IF YOUR FRIEND
IS DEAD.

04:30.303 --> 04:32.305
[  INDISTINCT SHOUTING  ]

04:33.906 --> 04:35.207
YEAH!

04:35.275 --> 04:37.944
[  SHOUTING CONTINUES  ]

04:38.010 --> 04:40.346
MARY JO?

04:40.413 --> 04:41.914
THEY´RE AT THE GOAT HOUSE.

04:41.981 --> 04:43.950
WHAT ARE THEY DOING TO MY HOUSE?

04:44.016 --> 04:46.286
SOMEBODY CALL THE POLICE!

04:46.353 --> 04:47.387
THE POLICE?

04:47.454 --> 04:49.423
DO -- DO YOU SEE WHAT´S GOING ON
OUT THERE?

04:49.489 --> 04:50.423
Y-YES.

04:50.490 --> 04:52.425
THE POLICE ARE USELESS.

04:52.492 --> 04:55.962
THAD, THE ONLY PEOPLE
WHO CAN STOP THEM IS US.

04:56.028 --> 04:57.297
[  INDISTINCT SHOUTING  ]

04:57.364 --> 04:58.898
ALL THE WORK I´VE DONE

04:58.965 --> 05:01.267
TO TURN B.M.S. INTO
A RESPECTABLE INSTITUTION

05:01.334 --> 05:03.936
IS BEING DESTROYED
ON NATIONAL TELEVISION,

05:04.003 --> 05:05.372
AND IT´S YOUR FAULT.

05:06.906 --> 05:08.808
I THINK IT´S ROMANTIC.

05:08.875 --> 05:13.246
US TRAPPED IN THIS ROOM,
DANGER RIGHT OUTSIDE THE DOOR.

05:13.313 --> 05:14.681
ANYTHING COULD HAPPEN.

05:14.747 --> 05:15.781
YOU´RE RIGHT, DEBRA.

05:15.848 --> 05:17.917
MAYBE THOSE MANIACS
WILL BURST IN HERE

05:17.984 --> 05:20.520
AND BEAT US TO DEATH
WITH A BLOCKING SLED.

05:20.587 --> 05:22.489
HOW ROMANTIC!

05:25.492 --> 05:28.728
THIS ISN´T JUST ABOUT SAMMY
AND MARY JO.

05:28.795 --> 05:31.598
IF THE GOAT HOUSE GETS
DESTROYED, WE LOSE EVERYTHING --

05:31.664 --> 05:36.902
THE BEER, THE DRUGS, OUR HOME.

05:36.969 --> 05:38.438
STOP!

05:38.505 --> 05:40.540
YOU HAD ME AT DRUGS.

05:41.641 --> 05:43.543
ME TOO.

05:43.610 --> 05:45.044
THANK YOU, DONNIE.

05:45.111 --> 05:48.047
YOU GUYS ARE GONNA NEED
A BETTER LEADER THAN MORAN.

05:48.114 --> 05:50.917
SO YOU HAVE MY SWORD.

05:50.983 --> 05:52.718
MINE TOO.

05:52.785 --> 05:54.820
GREAT. OKAY.
CAN WE GO?

05:57.524 --> 06:01.027
DO NOT LET OUR TALE GO UNTOLD.

06:01.093 --> 06:03.796
ESPECIALLY MINE.
I GOT THE GAME BALL TODAY, SO...

06:03.863 --> 06:06.733
ALL RIGHT.
COME ON. PLEASE.

06:06.799 --> 06:08.801
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS ]

06:14.006 --> 06:16.075
SHH!

06:16.142 --> 06:19.746
ALL RIGHT, SO, THE GOAT HOUSE
IS HALF A MILE THAT WAY.

06:19.812 --> 06:21.581
WE CAN SNEAK ACROSS CAMPUS

06:21.648 --> 06:22.816
THROUGH THESE BUILDINGS,
ALL RIGHT?

06:22.882 --> 06:25.585
MORAN, THE DAY YOU SAVE THE GAME
WITH THAT GOAL-LINE STAND

06:25.652 --> 06:27.487
AFTER I FUMBLE
ON OUR OWN 1-YARD LINE

06:27.554 --> 06:29.656
IS THE DAY I START
LISTENING TO YOU.

06:29.722 --> 06:32.925
THERE´S NOTHING TO BE SCARED OF.

06:32.992 --> 06:34.393
REALLY?

06:34.461 --> 06:35.829
[ SCREAMS ]

06:35.895 --> 06:37.464
OH, DID YOU SEE THAT?

06:37.530 --> 06:38.598
Shh!

06:38.665 --> 06:40.567
Don´t move.

06:40.633 --> 06:43.569
[ SCREAMING ]

06:43.636 --> 06:44.970
-B.M.S.!
-B.M.S.!
-B.M.S.!

06:45.037 --> 06:46.572
YEAH!

06:46.639 --> 06:48.040
FOOTBALL PLAYERS.

06:48.107 --> 06:50.376
-FOOTBALL PLAYERS!
-FOOTBALL PLAYERS!
-FOOTBALL PLAYERS!

06:50.443 --> 06:52.044
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING,
SCREAMING ]

06:52.111 --> 06:54.647
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO, GO, GO!

07:01.187 --> 07:03.189
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT HERE!

07:04.891 --> 07:06.460
NO! NO!

07:06.526 --> 07:08.695
-TAKE ME! TAKE ME!
-NO, NO, LARRY!

07:08.761 --> 07:10.129
NO, LARRY!
NO, LARRY!

07:10.196 --> 07:12.966
SAVE THE GOAT HOUSE!
SAVE THE GOAT HOUSE!

07:13.032 --> 07:15.401
SAVE THE GOAT HOUSE!

07:15.468 --> 07:16.669
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

07:23.009 --> 07:28.448
BRING...OUT...THE...GOAT!

07:28.515 --> 07:30.650
GET THE GOAT!

07:30.717 --> 07:32.652
GET THE GOAT!

07:32.719 --> 07:34.454
GET THE GOAT!

07:34.521 --> 07:35.989
GET THE GOAT!

07:36.055 --> 07:37.123
WHOA!

07:37.189 --> 07:39.859
IF THEY GET THROUGH THAT DOOR,
I´M A DEAD MAN!

07:39.926 --> 07:41.995
THEY´RE SO DRUNK
AND BLINDED BY JOY,

07:42.061 --> 07:44.030
THEY´VE STOPPED SEEING YOU
AS A HUMAN BEING.

07:44.096 --> 07:46.699
TO THEM, YOU´RE JUST THE GOAT.

07:46.766 --> 07:48.701
THEY WANT THE GOAT´S BLOOD.

07:48.768 --> 07:50.503
NOTHING ELSE WILL DO.

08:05.618 --> 08:08.554
I WANT A DYING WISH.

08:09.822 --> 08:11.557
WHAT KIND OF A WISH?

08:11.624 --> 08:13.926
UM...NOT REALLY SURE YET.

08:13.993 --> 08:16.929
SO, WHY DON´T WE ALL
HAVE A DRINK,

08:16.996 --> 08:20.667
AND, YOU KNOW,
WE CAN TALK ABOUT IT?

08:26.539 --> 08:29.875
WELL, THIS BRINGS BACK
OLD MEMORIES, DOESN´T IT?

08:29.942 --> 08:32.177
HOW CAN YOU TWO BE DRINKING
AT A TIME LIKE THIS?

08:32.244 --> 08:34.013
THIS IS OLD HAT FOR US.

08:34.080 --> 08:35.815
WE MET DURING ONE OF THESE.

08:35.882 --> 08:37.584
YOU MET DURING A RIOT?

08:37.650 --> 08:39.852
YEAH. IT WAS MY FIRST YEAR
OF COACHING.

08:39.919 --> 08:42.722
OH, AND I WAS
A FRESHMAN CHEERLEADER.

08:42.789 --> 08:44.824
MY BOYFRIEND WAS PINNED
UNDER HIS MUSTANG

08:44.891 --> 08:46.159
AFTER THE RIOTERS FLIPPED IT.

08:46.225 --> 08:48.895
AND I PULLED HER
INTO THIS VERY LOCKER ROOM.

08:48.961 --> 08:51.030
AM I THE ONLY ONE WHO CARES
THAT THIS SCHOOL IS BURNING?

08:51.097 --> 08:52.966
[ SIGHS ]
HE SAVED MY LIFE.

08:53.032 --> 08:54.500
HOW IS THIS HAPPENING?

08:54.567 --> 08:56.602
I TOOK EVERY PRECAUTION
TO KEEP THINGS SAFE.

08:56.669 --> 08:58.871
I EVEN HAD THEM STOP
SERVING ALCOHOL AT HALFTIME.

08:58.938 --> 08:59.972
YOU DID WHAT?

09:00.039 --> 09:04.010
YOU DON´T CUT OFF A STADIUM
FULL OF B.M.S. FANS AT HALFTIME.

09:04.076 --> 09:05.745
ARE YOU NUTS?

09:05.812 --> 09:07.614
I MEAN, NOW THEY´RE DRUNK ENOUGH
TO RIOT,

09:07.680 --> 09:09.481
BUT THEY´RE NOT DRUNK ENOUGH
TO PASS OUT.

09:09.549 --> 09:10.717
DON´T YOU RAISE YOUR VOICE
TO ME, MARTY.

09:10.783 --> 09:11.717
I´M STILL YOUR BOSS.

09:11.784 --> 09:13.986
WARREN, HONEY, LISTEN TO ME.

09:14.053 --> 09:16.756
YOU´RE ALWAYS TALKING ABOUT HOW
THE STUDENTS RESPECT YOU, RIGHT?

09:16.823 --> 09:17.891
YEAH.

09:17.957 --> 09:20.192
YOU NEED TO GO OUT THERE
AND TALK TO THEM, OKAY?

09:20.259 --> 09:22.629
FINE.

09:22.695 --> 09:26.632
DEAN SIMON TO THE RESCUE...

09:26.699 --> 09:27.867
AGAIN.

09:30.202 --> 09:31.871
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

09:36.275 --> 09:38.144
NO! NO, LARRY!

09:38.210 --> 09:39.812
HE´S GONE.
FORGET ABOUT HIM.

09:39.879 --> 09:40.947
HE´S GONE, MAN!

09:41.013 --> 09:43.182
NO.

09:43.249 --> 09:45.819
CAN WE GO BACK
TO THE LOCKER ROOM, PLEASE?

09:45.885 --> 09:47.587
NO, WE´VE GOT TO KEEP MOVING.

09:47.654 --> 09:48.755
MORAN´S RIGHT.

09:48.821 --> 09:51.857
HOW ELSE IS THE WORLD GONNA KNOW
THAT I GOT THE GAME BALL?

09:51.924 --> 09:53.593
LET´S GO!

09:53.660 --> 09:55.829
COME ON, DONNIE.
LET´S GO.

09:55.895 --> 09:57.529
WHOA. OH, GUYS,
CHECK IT OUT -- FOOD.

09:57.597 --> 09:58.865
-I HAVEN´T EATEN SINCE HALFTIME.
-DONNIE, WE GOT TO GO. COME ON.

09:58.931 --> 10:00.299
YOU KNOW HOW
MY BLOOD SUGAR GETS!

10:00.366 --> 10:02.301
CHIPS OR CHOCOLATE?
CHIPS OR CHOCOLATE?

10:02.368 --> 10:03.970
[ GRUNTING ]

10:04.036 --> 10:05.871
COME ON!
WE GOT TO GO, DONNIE!

10:05.938 --> 10:07.907
I GOT IT! I GOT IT, GUYS.
I GOT IT.

10:07.974 --> 10:09.008
[ LAUGHING ]

10:09.075 --> 10:10.309
-OKAY. GOOD.
-I´M STUCK.

10:10.376 --> 10:11.177
WHAT?

10:11.243 --> 10:12.244
ALEX, I´M STUCK.

10:12.311 --> 10:14.614
ALEX! HARMON!

10:14.681 --> 10:16.750
THAD, HELP ME!

10:16.816 --> 10:17.717
-HELP ME!
-DONNIE!

10:17.784 --> 10:19.719
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

10:25.224 --> 10:26.826
[ R&B PLAYS ]

10:26.893 --> 10:29.128
OH, YEAH.
THERE IT IS.

10:29.195 --> 10:32.065
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY
YOU SHOULD LIVE EACH DAY

10:32.131 --> 10:33.900
LIKE IT COULD BE YOUR LAST.

10:33.966 --> 10:36.969
BUT, UH, WE NEVER REALLY DO.

10:37.036 --> 10:39.138
-[ GLASS SHATTERS ]
-[ SCREAMING ]

10:39.205 --> 10:41.207
OH, MY GOD!
HOLY SHIT!

10:41.273 --> 10:42.074
WOW!

10:42.141 --> 10:44.711
GOD DAMN IT!
WOW!

10:44.777 --> 10:48.681
SAMMY, I KNOW WHAT YOU´RE DOING,
AND I LOVE IT.

10:48.748 --> 10:49.816
WHAT CAN I DO TO HELP?

10:49.882 --> 10:51.150
MARY JO, I´VE GOT EVERYTHING
UNDER CONTROL.

10:51.217 --> 10:52.385
-DON´T YOU WORRY --
-12-0!

10:53.052 --> 10:54.654
[ GRUNTS ]

10:54.721 --> 10:56.022
RIGHT.

10:56.088 --> 10:57.056
YOU PROTECT THE GOAT HOUSE.

10:57.123 --> 10:58.958
I´M GONNA TRY AND GO BANG
THOSE CHEERLEADERS.

11:01.360 --> 11:03.796
REMEMBER, DON´T USE CONDOMS.

11:03.863 --> 11:05.898
THEY´RE A WASTE OF TIME
IN A SITUATION LIKE THIS.

11:05.965 --> 11:08.300
RIGHT.

11:09.969 --> 11:11.904
HARMON, GET THE DOOR.

11:13.840 --> 11:16.309
OH, GREAT, THE BOOK ROOM?

11:16.375 --> 11:17.844
CAN´T WE FIND SOMEWHERE ELSE
TO HIDE?

11:17.910 --> 11:19.244
THIS IS MY LEAST FAVORITE ROOM
ON CAMPUS.

11:19.311 --> 11:21.881
THIS IS THE SAFEST PLACE
ON CAMPUS DURING A RIOT.

11:21.948 --> 11:23.216
NO ONE PARTIES IN HERE.

11:23.282 --> 11:26.786
I CAN´T STOP THINKING ABOUT THE
DRUGS AND THE BOOZE, YOU GUYS.

11:26.853 --> 11:29.956
I MEAN, THE HARDEST PART
IS NOT KNOWING.

11:30.022 --> 11:31.690
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

11:32.925 --> 11:35.728
I REMEMBER THE FIRST TIME
I DID SHROOMS.

11:35.795 --> 11:37.163
I WAS 10.

11:37.229 --> 11:40.699
MY UNCLE DENNIS SOLD THEM TO ME
AT MY MOM´S BIRTHDAY PARTY.

11:40.767 --> 11:42.368
I WAS TRIPPING SO HARD,

11:42.434 --> 11:46.371
I THOUGHT THE DEVILED EGGS
WERE TRYING TO SUCK ON MY BALLS.

11:46.438 --> 11:47.807
DO YOU KNOW WHAT?

11:47.874 --> 11:51.845
I LET ´EM,
´CAUSE IT FELT FANTASTIC.

11:52.979 --> 11:56.649
THE FIRST TIME I MET SAMMY,
I THOUGHT HE WAS DEAD.

11:56.715 --> 11:58.717
WE WENT TO SUMMER CAMP TOGETHER.

11:58.785 --> 12:01.988
THE BIG KIDS KEPT DUNKING
HIS HEAD IN THE LAKE

12:02.054 --> 12:03.388
OVER AND OVER AGAIN.

12:03.455 --> 12:05.057
HIS BODY WENT LIMP.

12:05.124 --> 12:07.259
EVERYONE THOUGHT HE WAS GONE.

12:07.326 --> 12:09.428
THEN THE NURSE
GAVE HIM MOUTH-TO-MOUTH

12:09.495 --> 12:11.330
AND BROUGHT HIM BACK.

12:12.799 --> 12:14.768
I FOUND OUT LATER
HE WAS FAKING THE WHOLE THING

12:14.834 --> 12:16.468
SO HE COULD MAKE OUT
WITH THE HOT NURSE.

12:18.137 --> 12:22.775
THAT´S WHEN HE BECAME MY HERO,
MY BEST FRIEND.

12:24.476 --> 12:27.446
I´VE LIVED IN THE GOAT HOUSE
SINCE MY FRESHMAN YEAR.

12:27.513 --> 12:29.315
AND I CARRY THE FLAME

12:29.381 --> 12:32.151
OF ALL THE CAPTAINS
THAT HAVE GONE BEFORE ME.

12:33.886 --> 12:37.222
I WILL NOT LET THAT GO OUT
ON MY WATCH.

12:40.526 --> 12:41.961
SHIT.

12:42.028 --> 12:43.296
THEY´RE STORMING THE LIBRARY.

12:43.362 --> 12:45.031
-GET UP. GET UP.
-YOU SAID NOBODY COMES HERE.

12:45.097 --> 12:46.465
WELL, I DIDN´T KNOW
THEY WERE GONNA FIND US!

12:46.532 --> 12:47.766
MAYBE THEY READ MY BLOG.

12:47.834 --> 12:50.136
YOU GAVE OUR WHEREABOUTS TO THEM
ON A BLOG?

